        "text": "We had the best experience working with Noah for our elopement photos! He made us feel so comfortable, kept everything fun, and captured our day perfectly. We got our photos back in two weeks, and we are obsessed. We highly recommend him!!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2023-08",
        "text": "Noah was absolutely amazing to work with. My husband and I had a micro wedding in Boulder this past June, and Noah captured our day beautifully. After the ceremony at Sunrise Amphitheater, we went up to Lost Gulch and he made our couples shots feel completely natural. We completely and strongly recommend Walnut Street Photography! Absolutely beautiful work and so much fun to work with."
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2024-09",
        "text": "We booked Walnut Street Photography while planning our wedding with Colorado Micro-Weddings. Noah was absolutely amazing to work with!  My husband and I are SO happy with how our photos turned out. Noah was wonderful and made things so easy for us on our wedding day. We are not from the area, so he arranged to bring our wedding flowers from the florist to us before our ceremony. He was so attentive and made us feel very comfortable while having our wedding photos taken. We will definitely be booking with Noah if we are back in the area and need photos taken again!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2023-10",
        "text": "Noah is FANTASTIC and produces STUNNING photos! As a bride who had never met her photographer prior to the big day, I obviously had reservations but he made our wedding that much more special! He’s personable, reliable and FAST with photo turnaround! 10/10 recommend!"
      },
      {
        "rating": 5,
        "when": "2023-11",
        "text": "Noah was referred to us by our wedding coordinator, Iver with Colorado Micro-Weddings. When I tell you we were blown away with the portraits he took of us to us we meant it. Noah went above and beyond on the day of our wedding. He drove us up the mountain for our portraits, assisted my family in putting on boutonnieres, and even placed my veil in my hair. Any minor detail Noah was there to help. Not to mention, he traveled from Denver to Breckenridge and even picked up my flowers on his way out there.  He captured our wedding day in such a beautiful way. I am so thankful our photos turned out better than I could ever imagine. Thank you Noah! Book with Walnut Street Photography!"
      }
